Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving the performance of heterogeneous graph processing systems through GPU acceleration. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as large scale graph processing is often used in database applications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a new algorithm for improving the efficiency of heterogeneous graph processing. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of GPUs for high-performance computing. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of GPU-accelerated heterogeneous architecture.
